translated: Jonsson, Gustav Sigfrid, provincial doctor, Mörtfors, born on November 17, 1900 in Nysätra, Västerbotten County, son of elementary school teacher Gustaf J. and Märta Larsson. Married in 1930 to jur. cand. Lilly Henrietta Catharina Sterner. They have one child: Nils Gustav Emil, born in 1931. Gustav passed his studentexamen in Umeå in 1919, received his medical degree in Uppsala in 1923, and his medical license there in 1929. He worked as an acting assistant at the pathology institute in Uppsala from 1927-1928, temporary provincial doctor in Nysätra and Robertsfors district in 1929, assistant doctor at Varberg Hospital in 1930, acting assistant at the pathology institute in Uppsala from 1930-1931, assistant doctor at Eksjö sanatorium from 1931-1932, assistant doctor at the surgical ward of Sahlgr. Hospital in 1932-1933, voluntary assistant at the bacteriological laboratory of the health board in Gothenburg, and an assistant doctor at the Carlanderska Hospital in 1933. He served as an assistant doctor at the Styrsö Coast Anatomy in 1934-1935, with brief assignments as an associate doctor at Falkenberg's, Varberg's, Bäckefors', and Mölndal's hospitals, Gothenburg's maternity ward, and Ekmanska hospital in Gothenburg in 1935-1936, and as an associate doctor at Mölndal's hospital from 1937-1940. Gustav was a temporary assistant doctor at Gothenburg's epidemic hospital in 1940, temporary provincial doctor in Båstad district in 1941, and a provincial doctor in Mörtfors district since 1942.
